---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Troubleshooting" description="Troubleshooting guide for TAOM - Tales From the Age of Men">
  <div class="page-content">
    <h1>Troubleshooting</h1>
    <p class="intro">Having issues with TAOM? Check the guides below for common problems and solutions.</p>

    <section class="load-order-section">
      <h2>Load Order</h2>
      <p class="version-note">Bannerlord Version <strong>1.2.12</strong></p>
      <ol class="load-order">
        <li><span class="mod-name">Harmony</span> <span class="mod-version">v2.3.6.220</span></li>
        <li>
          <span class="mod-name">Palatinr Debugger</span>
          <span class="mod-note">Writes to a log on crash — share the log with us to help diagnose</span>
        </li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">BetterExceptionWindow</span> <span class="mod-version">v7.1.1.0</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">ButterLib</span> <span class="mod-version">v2.10.0.0</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">UIExtenderEx</span> <span class="mod-version">v2.13.0.0</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">MCM</span> <span class="mod-version">v5.11.3.0</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">Native</span> <span class="mod-version">1.2.12.X</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">Sandbox Core</span> <span class="mod-version">1.2.12.X</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">Sandbox</span> <span class="mod-version">1.2.12.X</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">StoryMode</span> <span class="mod-version">1.2.12.X</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">CustomBattle</span> <span class="mod-version">1.2.12.X</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">Birth and Aging Options</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">LOTR_Map</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">LOTRAOM_Armory</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">Alliance.Wargs</span></li>
        <li><span class="mod-name">LOTRAOM</span> <span class="mod-version">0.69.39</span></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section warning-section">
      <h2>Disable Naval DLC</h2>
      <p>
        The Naval DLC is <strong>not compatible</strong> with TAOM and can cause crashes or broken gameplay. Steam sometimes
        re-enables it automatically after updates.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Before every play session</strong>, check your Bannerlord launcher and make sure the Naval DLC module is <strong
          >unchecked / disabled</strong
        >. While you're there, verify your full load order matches the one above.
      </p>
      <p class="tip-note">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> If you're experiencing unexplained crashes after a Steam update, this is the first thing to
        check.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>Delete Cached Shaders</h2>
      <p>
        If you have played this mod before, it is recommended you delete your cached shaders to avoid graphical issues.
      </p>
      <div class="path-block">
        <code>C:\ProgramData\Mount and Blade II Bannerlord\Shaders\TerrainShaders\LOTR_Map</code>
      </div>
      <p class="tip-note">
        <strong>Note:</strong>
        <code>ProgramData</code> is a hidden folder. You can paste the path directly into File Explorer's address bar to navigate
        to it.
      </p>
      <p class="tip-note">
        Delete this entire folder, then launch the game. Shaders will be regenerated automatically.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>Texture Creation Failure</h2>
      <p>If you see the following error on launch:</p>
      <img
        src="/images/troubleshooting-texture-error.png"
        alt="GPU_device::create_texture_array failed error"
        class="error-screenshot"
      />
      <h3>Fix</h3>
      <p>Set <strong>Terrain Quality</strong> in your game settings to <strong>Medium</strong> or higher.</p>
      <h3>Other GPU / Texture Errors</h3>
      <p>If you encounter any other GPU or texture-related errors, delete the entire Shaders folder:</p>
      <div class="path-block">
        <code>C:\ProgramData\Mount and Blade II Bannerlord\Shaders</code>
      </div>
      <p class="tip-note">
        <strong>Note:</strong>
        <code>ProgramData</code> is a hidden folder. Paste the path directly into File Explorer's address bar.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>DLL File Error — "Cannot load"</h2>
      <p>If you see an error like this:</p>
      <img src="/images/troubleshooting-dll-error.png" alt="Cannot load DLL file error" class="error-screenshot" />
      <p>This means Windows has blocked the mod's DLL files. You need to unblock them.</p>
      <h3>Fix (PowerShell — Recommended)</h3>
      <p>Open PowerShell <strong>as Administrator</strong> and run:</p>
      <div class="path-block">
        <code
          >gci -Path "C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Mount & Blade II Bannerlord\Modules" -Recurse |
          Unblock-File</code
        >
      </div>
      <p class="tip-note">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Change the drive letter if your game is installed on a different drive.
      </p>
      <h3>Fix (Manual)</h3>
      <p>You can also unblock files individually:</p>
      <ol class="steps-list">
        <li>Navigate to the DLL file shown in the error</li>
        <li>Right-click the file and select <strong>Properties</strong></li>
        <li>At the bottom of the General tab, check <strong>Unblock</strong></li>
        <li>Click <strong>Apply</strong></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>Names Replaced with Native Bannerlord Names</h2>
      <p><strong>Q: Why are the names in the mod replaced with ones from native Bannerlord?</strong></p>
      <ul class="steps-list">
        <li>
          The mod is currently only supported in <strong>English</strong>. Make sure your game language is set to
          English.
        </li>
        <li>
          If your language is already set to English and you still have this problem, you are most likely missing files
          and need to <strong>redownload the mod</strong>.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>Performance Issues</h2>
      <h3>Campaign Map FPS Drop</h3>
      <p>If you experience low FPS or stuttering on the campaign map:</p>
      <ol class="steps-list">
        <li>Open the game <strong>Options</strong> menu</li>
        <li>Start by unchecking <strong>Strategic AI</strong></li>
        <li>If that doesn't help, re-enable it and try disabling other options one by one</li>
        <li>This will help you identify which setting is causing the performance issue</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>Long Loading Screen / Horse Stopped Moving</h2>
      <p><strong>Q: I'm stuck on a loading screen, is this normal?</strong></p>
      <p><strong>Q: I load the game and the horse in the bottom right has stopped moving, is that normal?</strong></p>
      <p>
        Yes — each time you run the mod after a new or fresh download, the game needs to compile all of the files,
        shaders, and code. This is a one-time process and can take anywhere from <strong
          >ten minutes to two hours</strong
        > depending on your hardware.
      </p>
      <p>Be patient and let it finish. Subsequent launches will be much faster.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>My Game is Crashing</h2>
      <p>If your game crashes, follow these steps so we can help diagnose the issue:</p>
      <ol class="steps-list">
        <li>When the crash report appears, <strong>save the report as HTML</strong></li>
        <li>Go to our <a href="/community">Discord server</a></li>
        <li>Open a <strong>support ticket</strong></li>
        <li>
          Include your <strong>load order</strong>, what you were doing when it crashed (context), and attach the crash
          report
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>We will help you as we are available.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section">
      <h2>Where is the Music?</h2>
      <p><strong>Q: The game has no music / where is the custom soundtrack?</strong></p>
      <p>
        We are actively working on a custom soundtrack. Unfortunately, Bannerlord 1.2.12 requires replacing the <em
          >entire</em
        > soundtrack to add custom music — there's no way to add tracks individually. This limitation may change in version
        1.3.
      </p>
      <p>For now, the mod ships without custom music. Stay tuned for updates.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="topics-grid">
      <!-- Subpages will be added here as cards -->
    </div>

    <p class="still-stuck">Still stuck? Join our <a href="/community">Discord community</a> for help.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h1 {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .intro {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .topics-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .load-order-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .load-order-section h2 {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .version-note {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .load-order {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: load-order;
    padding: 0;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .load-order li {
    counter-increment: load-order;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .load-order li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .load-order li::before {
    content: counter(load-order);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    min-width: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .mod-name {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .mod-version {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-family: monospace;
  }

  .mod-note {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .tip-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .warning-section {
    background: rgba(212, 162, 76, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(212, 162, 76, 0.25);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .tip-section h2 {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tip-section p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .path-block {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .path-block code {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-family: monospace;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .tip-section h3 {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .error-screenshot {
    display: block;
    max-width: 450px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .steps-list {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .steps-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .tip-note {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .still-stuck {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .still-stuck a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .still-stuck a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
